<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/docbook-ng">
<title>Introduction</title>

    <para>
    CLI is a library and a set of tools
    that allow you to easily develop text-based user interfaces.
    So far, what you have to do is
        <orderedlist>
        <listitem>writing an XML resource file;</listitem>
        <listitem>transforming it using the tools of the library;</listitem>
        <listitem>plugging it into an existing program.</listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    These points are discussed in the <link linkend="howto">first section</link>.
    </para>

    <para>
    <link linkend="xmlres">Second section</link> is a reference manual for XML resource files syntax.
    </para>

    <para>
    <link linkend="more">Last section</link> gives advanced information
    for users having specific needs.
    </para>

</section>
